Install Python: Ensure you have Python installed on your system.
Install Flask and Pandas using commond prompt.
Create the file "app.py"
Create a directory called 'Project' which contain the file "app.py". 
Create another directory called 'templates' inside directory 'Project' which contain the file "index.html" and "result.html"
Create another directory called 'static' inside directory 'Project' which contain a favicon.
IT WILL LOOK LIKE THIS:-
Project/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── index.html
│   └── result.html
├── static/
└── uploads/

Navigate to your project directory in the command prompt or terminal.
Run the application with: python app.py
Open a web browser and navigate to http://127.0.0.1:5000.
upload the groups.csv and hostels.csv files.
The application will process the files, display the allocation results, and provide a download link for the allocation details.
